```make run-golden-test-runner TOKEN=8m9MyX6w988CX2rO14uMQUK2sXCjau USERNAME=goldens-tester SKIP_TESTS= TEST_ENV=localhost INPUT_PATH='ib_eng/tests/fs/Test Drive' TEST_NAMES='mixed-pdf-provenance-test'```
and the error I get is
```Error uploading golden-test zip file. Response: {'status': 'ERROR', 'statusCode': 400, 'msg': 'Token owner does not have permission to view repo tests.'}```
Currently I'm using a token called "dogfood_testing2" that I created in OAuth apps under admin settings in instabase. I didn't have any pre-existing tokens to use. I've also been added to both the Instabase employees and doc insights groups on instabase. Does anyone know how to fix this permissions issue / generate a token that would work?
I run into this new error "KeyError: 'status'"
but I think it got past the permissions
Yup looks like it got past permissions, KeyError in the "status" field will be more related to a failing api endpoint
